### Per-category quality bar (minimum)

- **Sciences** (physics, chemistry, biology, natural_science): one law / formula / organism / process per question; numeric answers must differ across the batch.
- **Mathematics**: distinct problem statements and answers; no copy-paste with changed coefficients unless each is a deliberate standalone problem.
- **Geography / continents**: real named locations; map facts to ml.wikipedia district/state/country names.
- **History** (world, Indian, Kerala): correct agent, patient, verb (§3); no vague `യുദ്ധം` when a named battle exists.
- **Economics / banking**: PSC-style “which scheme / which institution / which year” — not nested `സൂചിപ്പിക്കുന്നു` definitions.
- **Kerala politics / districts / renaissance**: Malayalam names for people and places; no English-only distractors.
- **Literature / cinema / arts**: titles in source language; authors/directors verified.
- **Current affairs**: dated file (`current_affairs_2026_06.json`); facts from that month only; update manifest if adding months.

### Post-generation validation (run before merge)

```bash
# Malayalam quality
python3 apply_malayalam_rules.py <file>.json

# Filler smell tests (adjust pattern per category)
rg "പ്രദേശം-\d+|വസ്തുത-\d+|ക്ഷുദ്രഗ്രഹം [^\s']+-\d+|ഗാലക്സി NGC-\d+" <file>.json
rg "സൂചിപ്പിക്കുന്ന പ്രവർത്തി|നടത്തുന്ന സേവനം" <file>.json

# Duplicate stems within file
python3 -c "
import json; from collections import Counter
qs=[q['question'] for q in json.load(open('<file>.json'))['questions']]
d=[s for s,c in Counter(qs).items() if c>1]
print('dupes', len(d))
"
```

If filler grep returns hits or duplicate stems > 0, fix before considering the category complete.

## 6. Research and verification — use the internet

**Always verify facts and Malayalam wording online** before adding or editing questions. Prefer Malayalam sources so spelling, terms, and phrasing match exam usage.

### Primary sources (use first)

| Source | Use for |
|--------|---------|
| [Malayalam Wikipedia](https://ml.wikipedia.org) | Facts, dates, names, places, Malayalam terminology |
| [സർവ്വവിജ്ഞാനകോശം / Sarvavijnanakosam](https://www.sarvavijnanakosam.in) | Authoritative Malayalam encyclopedia entries, Kerala & India topics |
| Other Malayalam references | Government portals (`.gov.in`, Kerala `.kerala.gov.in`), Kerala PSC syllabi, reputed Malayalam news sites |

### Secondary sources (when Malayalam entry is missing or thin)

- [English Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org) — cross-check facts only; **rewrite** the question in Malayalam using terms from Malayalam Wikipedia where they exist.
- Official org sites (ISRO, RBI, FIFA, etc.) for current data and scheme names.

### How to apply

1. Search the topic on **Malayalam Wikipedia** first; note standard Malayalam names and phrasing.
2. Cross-check dates, numbers, and spellings with a second source when possible.
3. Do **not** copy sentences verbatim — paraphrase into clear PSC-style Malayalam.
4. For book/author questions, confirm title language and spelling from Malayalam or original-language references.
5. For current affairs, prefer recent Malayalam news + official announcements over outdated entries.

```text
✅ ml.wikipedia.org → confirm person/place names and Malayalam terms before writing options
✅ Sarvavijnanakosam → confirm Kerala renaissance figure / work details
❌ Paste English Wikipedia sentence and translate word-for-word
❌ Guess dates or names without checking any source
```

## Quick review checklist

- [ ] Facts verified via Malayalam Wikipedia / Sarvavijnanakosam (or other reliable sources)
- [ ] Malayalam script throughout (except allowed terms and source-language book titles)
- [ ] Book/literary titles in their source language (English books in English, Malayalam in Malayalam)
- [ ] No Manglish or English sentence fragments
- [ ] No English-only questions; no mixed-language stems or options (`ഒന്നുമില്ല` + `BJP only`, etc.)
- [ ] Question unique across repo; **conceptually** unique (not same template + same answer repeated)
- [ ] No universal filler: `പ്രദേശം-N`, `വസ്തുത-N`, numbered fake entities, definition wrappers
- [ ] Category-specific rules applied (astronomy / geography / economics sections above)
- [ ] Four options, one correct answer, difficulty set; correct ID prefix for file
- [ ] `python3 apply_malayalam_rules.py <file>.json` run after bulk edits
- [ ] Reads naturally to a Malayalam speaker preparing for Kerala PSC–style exams
- [ ] Historical questions: correct agent/patient, event-appropriate verb, proper noun from Malayalam Wikipedia (not generic calque)
- [ ] Target count reached with real facts only — **never** padded with numbered templates
